value.name: 39 (number) - Wikipedia
value.snippet: 39 is the sum of five consecutive primes (3 + 5 + 7 + 11 + 13) and also is the product of the first and the last of those consecutive primes. Among small semiprimes only three other integers (10, 155, and 371) share this attribute. 39 also is the sum of the first three powers of 3 (3 1 + 3 2 + 3 3 ). Given 39, the Mertens function returns 0.

value.name: html - What is &#39; and why does Google search replace it with ...
value.snippet: Sorted by: 72. It's HTML character references for encoding a character by its decimal code point. Look at the ASCII table here and you'll see that 39 (hex 0x27, octal 47) is the code for apostrophe. Share. Improve this answer. Follow. edited Feb 21, 2021 at 12:26. answered Mar 28, 2015 at 6:08.

value.name: &#39 meaning explained: HTML coding issues causes confusion online - HITC
value.snippet: &#39 is the HTML character coding for an apostrophe (‘), so if you see “don&#39t” or “can&#39t” this means that the words “don’t” or “can’t” are being represented by ecards.

value.name: Ländervorwahl | Vorwahl: 0039 bzw. +39
value.snippet: Die Vorwahl 0039 bzw. die Ländervorwahl +39 gehört dem Land Italien. Um Telefonate aus Deutschland nach Italien führen zu können ist die Benutzung der internationalen Vorwahl 0039 obligatorisch. Um ein Telefonat nach Italien zu führen, geben Sie auf Ihrem Gerät zuerst die Ziffern der Landesvorwahl ein: 0039 .
